Package: geospatialsuite
Title: Comprehensive Geospatiotemporal Analysis and Multimodal Integration Toolkit
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person("Olatunde D.", "Akanbi", email = "olatunde.akanbi@case.edu", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7719-2619")), person("Vibha", "Mandayam", role = "aut"), person("Yinghui", "Wu", role = "aut", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3991-5155")), person("Jeffrey", "Yarus", role = "aut", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9331-9568")), person("Erika I.", "Barcelos", email = "erika.barcelos@case.edu", role = c("aut", "cph"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9273-8488")), person("Roger H.", "French", email = "roger.french@case.edu", role = c("aut", "cph"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6162-0532")))
Maintainer: Olatunde D. Akanbi <olatunde.akanbi@case.edu>
Description: A comprehensive toolkit for geospatiotemporal analysis featuring 60+ vegetation 
    indices, advanced raster visualization, universal spatial mapping, water quality
    analysis, CDL crop analysis, spatial interpolation, temporal analysis, and 
    terrain analysis. Designed for agricultural research, environmental
    monitoring, remote sensing applications, and publication-quality mapping with
    support for any geographic region and robust error handling.
    Funding: This material is based upon financial support by the National Science Foundation,
    EEC Division of Engineering Education and Centers, NSF Engineering Research Center for
    Advancing Sustainable and Distributed Fertilizer production (CASFER), NSF 20-553 Gen-4 
    Engineering Research Centers award 2133576.
